cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with cooperative games and their learnability. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the PAC learning model. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with predicting values of unseen coalitions. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the efficiency of learning different classes of cooperative games. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category as the paper studies network flow games and induced subgraph games.
